Definition.WordDefinition: Skeletonize \Skel"e*ton*ize\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Skeletonized}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Skeletonizing}.] To prepare a skeleton of; also, to reduce, as a leaf, to its skeleton. --Pop. Sci. Monthly. [1913 Webster]
